The second row refers to the same $W$ configuration where, however, any coherence between path-encoded and polarization-encoded qubits is removed. Correspondingly, ${\cal W}^W_2$ and ${\cal W}^W_3$ are below the threshold for separability, showing that in the the corresponding configuration we only have bipartite entanglement.  }
